frameDefinitions: An Object with an understood function is or is not in a state ready to perform that function.
The words in this frame refer to what Clothing the Wearer (or a specific Body_part of the Wearer) has on.
An Agent suddenly and often violently separates the Whole_patient into two or more smaller Pieces, resulting in the Whole_patient no longer existing as such.
An Agent changes Tools, from the Old_tool to a New_tool.
An Item is the only instance of its Type.
A System is perceived as complex depending on the intricacy of the interconnectivty of its parts or components.
frameExamples: I <t>had</t> <t>on</t> the most ridiculous monkey-suit you could imagine.
He <t>ripped</t> <t>up</t> the letter faster than you can say 'Jack Robbins'. INI
If this happens one more time, we 're going to <t>switch</t> operating systems.
Steven is the <t>sole</t> survivor in his family.
San Diego freeways are a <t>complex</t> array of poorly maintained roads.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity with an understood purpose.
The person whose clothing is under discussion.
This role identifies the <fen>Clothing</fen> that the <fen>Wearer</fen> wears.
The body part of the <fen>Wearer</fen> which is covered by the <fen>Clothing</fen>.
The time at or during which the <fen>Wearer</fen> has the <fen>Clothing</fen> on.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional action that results in the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> being broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The entity which is destroyed by the <fen>Agent</fen> and that ends up broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The fragments of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> that result from the <fen>Agent</fen>'s action.
An event which leads to the fragmentation of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks up the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> into pieces.
The individual that changes their situation.
The entities controlled by an Agent to achieve some Purpose.
The tool that the <fen>Agent</fen> had been using.
The tool that the <fen>Agent</fen> ends up using.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> makes a change.
An <fen>Item</fen> is alone in its category.
<fen>Type</fen> specifies a category which in principle could apply to multiple items, but which is limited to the <fen>Item</fen>.
The complete entity or system whose complexity is under consideration.
listRoleExamples: She was wearing a glove <fex>on one hand</fex>.
<fex>By five o'clock</fex>, he was wearing the old holey jeans and t-shirt again.
<fex>I and I alone</fex> can shatter the gem and break the curse.
Shattering someone's confidence is a little different than shattering <fex>a dish</fex>.
I smashed the toy boat <fex>to flinders</fex>.
